		<hr />
		
		
			<div><strong>Summary of Utility Suggestions for Wizards</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>I've tried to summarise the suggestions for adding utility to the wizard class from the patch day thread (<a href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=18737" target="_blank">http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=18737</a>).<br />
<br />
The discussion in the patch day thread focused heavily upon the change to the method of reaching the plane of hate, and the erosion over time of the transportation part of the wizard role. The thread reached 18 pages and included a lot of ideas for adding utility to the wizard class as compensation.<br />
<br />
These are not my personal suggestions, they are just copied into one place for convenience. They are individual ideas, roughly sorted into categories. Please feel free to discuss the suggestions or add further ideas.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Transportation to Plane of Hate and Sky</b><br />
<br />
•	Remove the reagent cost for wizards transporting to Hate and Sky<br />
•	Add gate spells to Hate and Sky<br />
•	Add translocate spells to Hate and Sky (recipient must have hate stone)<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>New Transportation Spells (possibly quested) / Transportation Changes</b><br />
<br />
•	New gate spells: Barindu, Chardok, PoTranquility, PoMischief and Western Wastes (or ToV)<br />
•	New port/TL spells: Barindu, PoTranquility, PoMischief, Runnyeye and Western Wastes (or ToV)<br />
•	Change the EJ and Skyfire evacuation spells to ports and add a gate and translocate to these destinations<br />
•	Self-gates to the wizard guilds in Qeynos, Freeport, Neriak, Erudin, Ak'Anon and Gukta (can make these quested)<br />
•	A gate to the Temple of Solusek Ro (quested or worshippers only)<br />
•	A port to the Tower of Solusek Ro (quested or worshippers only or both)<br />
•	Translocate Group and Teleport spells that work with a given location (Plane of Knowledge or Nexus would be most practical, or the original old world spires)<br />
•	MGB AA that would make group ports an AE TL to the cast point<br />
•	A gate spell that turns the caster invisible upon arrival<br />
•	Planar Ascension: Gates/ports/tlocs to some nice locations in PoP and above. Code the level/flag requirements for travel into zones that have them.<br />
•	Ability to translocate or port people to the WIZARD's bind point.<br />
•	Allow us to Decession people out of group with a confirmation box like TL.<br />
•	For omens make more portal locations that won't have books going to them.<br />
•	A second spell in addition to bind affinity that would bind our mind instead of our soul (so wizards could have two bind points).<br />
•	Raid Evacuation (could be problems with accidental raid evacuations though?)<br />
•	Make the landing for the Skyfire port safer (so there's less chance of aggro and chromadracs stripping buffs on landing)<br />
•	Make it possible for wizards to bind in more locations - not just cities (wizard-only ability)<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Anti-Gate Spell / Anti-Summon Spell / Silence Spell / Highsun Spell</b><br />
<br />
•	Anti-gate spell: Back in PoP beta there were ideas for an anchor sort of spell we could cast on mobs that would stop them from gating - I think we'd all like to see that actually make it to live, would give us a lot more utility use in raids and groups. This would go a long way to making people happy about our utility functions. (Gemdiver's words)<br />
•	Anti-summoning spell: A spell that stopped a mob from summoning for a certain amount of time<br />
•	A silence spell: It would stop the mobs from casting any spells, but it doesn't stop them from meleeing. For it to be worthwhile it would have to have one or more of the following:<br />
a) harder to resist than stun, or work on stun immune mobs<br />
b) longer duration than stun<br />
c) faster recast than stun so it could be chained more effectively<br />
•	Highsun spell: Ability to &quot;Highsun&quot; Mobs to their binds with an Aggro Wipe.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Damage Shields and Targetable Weapon Proc Spells</b><br />
<br />
•	Improve the O'Kiels damage shield line - significant damage increase.<br />
•	Group O'Kiels damage shield spells.<br />
•	A damage rune: Like the wizard skin rune only it's also a damage shield until its hit points are exhausted. Or a targetable damage rune with no protective component, but still has the mega damage shield until the hit points cap is reached? Long recast so we couldn't keep it up all the time.<br />
•	Targetable Xuzl-proc spell (not specified how this would work)<br />
•	Targetable weapon proc: a spell to cast on a melee character that adds a significant proc to their weapon (e.g. fire procs for high damage, ice procs for frequent procs with lower damage, magic procs for medium damage with a stun). Higher spells in the line proc for more damage and/or more often. Stacks with existing weapon procs. <br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Group Spells</b><br />
<br />
•	Group Spell Shield<br />
•	Group Calrena/Alendar<br />
•	Extend Flappy benefits to the entire group<br />
•	Group Harvest<br />
•	Endurance buff<br />
•	Spell-haste buff (self-only - or maybe a targetable one like the cleric line?)<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Invisibility Spells</b><br />
<br />
•	Group Invisibility<br />
•	Targetable Improved Invisibility<br />
•	Combined Invisibility and See Invisibility spell<br />
•	Invisibility AA: automatic invisibility upoon landing after a gate/port/translocate. It could have 3 levels (First level would only invis you upon landing after a gate. 2nd level would invis you and your group upon landing after a port. 3rd level would invis people upon landing from a TL).<br />
•	Phase Shift: Self-Target only. The wizard phases in and out of current time/space, allowing them move undetected by all creatures.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Knock / Shatter Lock Spell</b><br />
<br />
•	Knock / Shatter Lock spell: to open locked doors - a spell which allows the wizard to focus great energy, shattering open a locked door.<br />
•	Short group teleport to the other side of a locked door.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Combination Effect Spells</b><br />
<br />
•	Phase Lock: Single Target. An NPC is locked in between time/space rendering them motionless unable to be attacked/or attack.<br />
•	A spell that places a mob in a layer of Ice, effectively mezzing the MoB until the ice is shattered or melted.<br />
•	Temporal Disruption Spell: a spell line that is a nuke and a cast time increaser for targets 12% 25% 50% think of it as a spell based slow opposite to melee slow?<br />
•	Ice nuke with a percentage based slow 15% slow builds on each cast till 60%<br />
•	Fire nuke with a burn down after effect (dot)<br />
•	Magic nuke with a mana tap on casters mobs<br />
•	Frost Flame - Fire nuke with a cold debuff built in debuff is a 3 tick duration dot<br />
•	Burning Frost - Cold Nuke with a Fire debuff built in debuff is a 3 tick duration dot<br />
•	Coldsnap- AE cold based root<br />
•	AE fog (possibly for PvP)<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Eye of Zomm Spells</b><br />
<br />
•	Improved Eye of Xomm: improve duration and allow eye to swim (possibly equal to casters swimming skill).<br />
•	Targetable eye of Xomm (i.e. give another player their own temporary eye)<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Reflect Spells</b><br />
<br />
•	It was suggested that they are not very useful in their current format or only of rare situational use.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Stuns and Xuzl</b><br />
<br />
•	A Lure-based stun: that works on high level mobs for emergency use - could have long recast timer.<br />
•	PBAOE stun<br />
•	PBAOE Xuzl (not sure how this works?)<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Concussion</b><br />
<br />
•	AE concussion<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Wizard CoTH</b><br />
<br />
•	It fits in with the wizard's transportation role – and could help smaller guilds if another class had the CoTH ability.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Research</b><br />
<br />
•	Make all GoD spells researchable by wizards<br />
•	Research scrolls: Give research an alchemy like quality, so wizards can make tradable single charge gate scrolls to specific destinations. For example, &quot;Scroll of Alter plane:Hate&quot;: Stone, Quill, Parchent = Right click one charge gate to Hate scroll. <br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Manaburn</b><br />
<br />
•	Fix Manaburn (discussed in the wizard top 10 list)</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
