			<hr />
			
				Evacuate upgrades:<br />
Astral Bubble:<br />
Group Root+Invis (SoS-level)+Fade<br />
Cannot be clicked off, duration of 2 minutes.<br />
<br />
This is an evacuate-style spell that doesn't require crawling back to camp. After you cast it, you are stuck waiting around for 2 minutes, so people will only use it in emergencies.<br />
<br />
Astral Sphere:<br />
Same as Astral Bubble, but targetted on a single player (groupmate). Fast casting.<br />
<br />
Astral Fade:<br />
Self-only Astral Sphere.<br />
<br />
Astral Sphere can be used as a pseudo-coth for pullers, depending on range and how it works with aggro. It can also be used to save someone from death, but that would be much harder.<br />
<br />
Astral Fade will probably prove very popular with wizards. A 2 minute cooldown is much better than a death to a wizard. =) It also makes one think of the low level wizard spell line &quot;fade&quot; or &quot;shadowstep&quot;, but this spell actually works.
			
