		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Gnomish Greetings!<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2">
			<hr />
			
				I agree too, I really don't want more utility. I'd rather see a cold and magic nuke equal to our best fire nukes so we have equal options.
			
			<hr />
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
I don't think that needs to be a matter for exchange for utility.  I think as wizards we are by definition supposed to have the best nukes.  They vary the resist type with expansions to give certain mobs more challenge and give us a spell to look forward to for each new expansion.  I also think we need to keep in mind that there is a limit to the dps upgrades that can be handed out within each level cap without making newer content trivial.<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2">
			<hr />
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Inuisitr</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">it's not even that we need utility, it's that we're a one show pony right now....</div>
			
			<hr />
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
With transportation abilities really being trivial with PoK and new travel abilities being handed out without thought, we should think seriously about what utility would help with group desirability.  A lot of things on the list would seriously infringe on other classes abilities and SoE would be faced with the same situation with another class.  <br />
<br />
You can make the argument that everyone got transportation abilities, but just because we had the utility taken away is not a reason to take away someone else's utility.  The one stipulation given to any utility was that it can not infringe on another class's ability:<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2">
			<hr />
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Brenlo</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">What other utility ideas do you Wizard folk have that will not take away from another class? Let's see what we can come up with here and see what the team thinks.</div>
			
			<hr />
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
DPS upgrades will always be given away, it appears that transportation abilities will be as well.  People have just gotten used to fast travel  instead of braving the elements and taking effort to get to new areas; they are instead going to places that are easy to get to.  A long time ago the argument was that there was too much down time in the game and travel was one of the reasons.  They made changes to the game to compensate but our transportation utility was diminished as a result.<br />
<br />
When getting groups we are one of many dps classes, so what a group is likely to balance filling the spot is utility.  Some wizards do not care about grouping and only care about raiding.  For those that prefer to group, utility is going to help distinguish their dps from other classes' dps.<br />
<br />
It has been suggested before, and shot down but here it goes again:  There is one utility that has yet to be given to a class and that is Endurance Regeneration.  Wizards that have a desire to group should seriously consider lobbying for this ability.  We need interaction between the classes and probably the biggest rift between two class groups is the wizards and the melee.  Many other classes provide added value to the melee groups through haste, health regen and attack.  Wizards are severely lacking in this area.  Please, please please give this some thought.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
