It doesn't have to be a buff, but that would probably provide the most utility to the wizard class.  They could go any number of routes from a Paladin-like LoH innate ability to an AA for a pulse of replenishment like Paragon of the Spirit.  <br />
<br />
Buffs are not pointless or you wouldn't get any.  It seems, from previous discussions, that buffs are not counted toward the casters ability.  Take wizards for example.  Everyone assumes full mana regeneration buffs when calculating potential dps.  The dps is not attributed to the classes that cast the regen buffs (as it probably should in some cases).  Melee dps is calculated with buff haste but not attributed to the buffer.  These are things that other classes add to a group that a wizard does not have a comparable ability.<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
